com.wm.xmldata

Class XmlDataContentTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataTag
      • com.wm.xmldata.XmlDataContentTag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    XmlDataAnyTag, XmlDataElementTag, XmlDataGroupTag, XmlDataIteratorTag, XmlDataSubstitutionTag

    public class XmlDataContentTag
extends XmlDataTag
    This class is a common superclass for the XmlDataTags that may appear in content models. All XmlDataCursor methods that insert or change content typically expect a instance of some subclass of this class.

      • getPathName

        public java.lang.String getPathName()
        Description copied from class: XmlDataTag
        Returns the tag in path-name format. The path-name is the full-name which include particle-id, ncName, and namespace as well as additional properties used by XmlDataMap or XmlDataCopy. The additional properties are index and indirect-qualifier. Qualified names are returned in the form ncName#namespace. Index (if defined) is represented as [index] and indirect-qualifiers is defined re represented as {consent-tag}. If the namespace uses the path characters '[', ']', or '/', those characters are %-encoded using %2F for /, %5B for [, %5D for ], and %25 for %.
        Overrides:
        getPathName in class XmlDataTag
        Returns:
        a String representation of the path-name

      • getPathName

        public java.lang.String getPathName(XmlNamespaceMap nsDecls)
        Description copied from class: XmlDataTag
        Returns the tag in path-name form using namespace prefixes. The path-name is the full name with additional properties as it is used by XmlDataMap or XmlDataCopy. Qualified names are returned in the form prefix:ncName. The prefix is defined by the nsDecls argument
        Overrides:
